18 Oct 2008 07:31






Suggestions:

-"SCP-290 enjoys conversation, no personnel are permitted to talk to it, disregard of this order is suspension of 1 week minimum." should be within the Special Containment Procedures. Further, there should be some justification for why personnel are not allowed to talk to the SCP.

-"SCP-290 is to be held… at all times. SPC-290 is to never leave…" is a bit redundant. Perhaps these two sentences can be rephrased as "SCP-290 is to be held in a 10x10x10 holding cell located 20 meters underground at all times. SCP-290 is not to be permitted to come into contact with any organic matter."

-Why is it so important that SCP-290 kept away from organic material? Why does SCP-290 deserve the Keter class designation? These questions need to be answered within the description of the SCP, otherwise this SCP should be reclassified as Safe especially considering that it was captured with "no trouble at all'.







